GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 93
Short Title: Portability of Leave/Charter Schools. (Public)
Sponsors: Senators Hanig and Ford (Primary Sponsors).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
February 13, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO ALLOW SICK LEAVE AND VACATION LEAVE TO BE TRANSFERRED
3 BETWEEN A CHARTER SCHOOL AND A LOCAL SCHOOL ADMINISTRATIVE
4 UNIT.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6 SECTION 1.(a) Article 23 of Chapter 115C of the General Statutes is amended by
7 adding a new section to read:
8 "§ 115C-336.2. Transfer of leave.
9 The State Board shall adopt rules and regulations that allow sick leave and vacation leave to
10 be transferred between a charter school and a local school administrative unit. Leave to be
11 accepted by a local school administrative unit must not result in leave being accrued at a greater
12 rate than the rate set by the Board."
13 SECTION 1.(b) G.S. 115C-218.90(a) is amended by adding a new subdivision to
14 read:
15 "(7) Charter school employees shall be eligible for the transfer of sick leave and
16 vacation leave as provided under G.S. 115C-336.2."
17 SECTION 2. This act is effective when it becomes law and applies to individuals
18 employed by a local school administrative unit or a charter school on or after that date.
*S93-v-1*

